The paper deals with complex event processing (CEP) in data streams, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DB (Databases) is a likely category as CEP involves processing large amounts of data in real-time. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as the paper discusses adaptation mechanisms that monitor data properties and make decisions based on them. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method for dynamically deciding whether and how the evaluation structure should be reoptimized. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method. Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of known algorithms for evaluation plan generation.
